textBeforeTable: 2013 Men's Soccer Roster       Personal: Austin is the son of Richard and Sue Haire ... major is psychology ... born on Oct. 28, 1992. Prep: Capped off a successful prep career at Chesterton High School where he was named first team all-conference twice and first team all-district. Prior to HC: Spent two seasons at Prairie State (Ill.) College where he amassed a total of seven goals and six assists in 39 career games ... helped guide the Pioneers to a 19-3 record in his sophomore season ... was also named second team all-conference both seasons at Prairie State. 2013 Season Stats 2013: Saw action in 19 games during the season, starting in 18 … scored his first career goal in the 4-2 victory over Huntington (Sept. 12) … netted the game-winner against St. Francis (Oct. 22) … had a season-high three shots against Purdue Calumet (Nov. 2) … finished the year with 26 shots, 13 on net … tied for second on the team with five goals.   Hometown: Porter, Ind. Position: MID Class: JR Weight: 160 Height: 5-10 Haire #20 Austin
